<div dir="auto">
    <h2 class="mt-5">V engines</h2>
    <p>A <b>V engine</b>, sometimes called a <b>Vee engine</b>, is a common <a
            href="/wiki/Engine_configuration" title="Engine configuration">configuration</a>
        for <a href="/wiki/Internal_combustion_engine" title="Internal
            combustion engine">internal combustion engines</a>. It consists of
        two <a href="/wiki/Cylinder_bank" class="mw-redirect" title="Cylinder
            bank">cylinder banks</a>—usually with the same number of cylinders
        in each bank—connected to a common <a href="/wiki/Crankshaft"
            title="Crankshaft">crankshaft</a>. These cylinder banks are arranged
        at an angle to each other, so that the banks form a "V" shape when
        viewed from the front of the engine.
    </p>
